], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The pair\", \"from\": 2883, \"to\": 2891}, {\"ngram\": \"the WorldTour\", \"from\": 2934, \"to\": 2947}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tough-to-beat duo has claimed many 1-2 victories throughout the last two seasons, meaning they know each other's strengths and weaknesses very well.\", \"from\": 2949, \"to\": 3101, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"beat\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 2966}, {\"ngram\": \"many 1-2 victories\", \"from\": 2983, \"to\": 3001}, {\"ngram\": \"the last two seasons\", \"from\": 3013, \"to\": 3033}, {\"ngram\": \"each other's strengths\", \"from\": 3053, \"to\": 3075}, {\"ngram\": \"weaknesses\", \"from\": 3080, \"to\": 3090}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, they will be racing against one another and it will be interesting to see how they compete among their respective national teams.\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3106, \"end\": 3111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.65442159731475e-31, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their respective national teams\", \"from\": 3210, \"to\": 3241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Kopecky often plays more of a wildcard in her road races, Wiebes is typically in tune with a powerful lead-out that helps position her for sprint wins.\", \"from\": 3244, \"to\": 3401, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 3250, \"to\": 3257}, {\"ngram\": \"a wildcard\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3288}, {\"ngram\": \"her road races\", \"from\": 3292, \"to\": 3306}, {\"ngram\": \"Wiebes\", \"from\": 3308, \"to\": 3314}, {\"ngram\": \"tune\", \"from\": 3331, \"to\": 3335}, {\"ngram\": \"a powerful lead-out\", \"from\": 3341, \"to\": 3360}, {\"ngram\": \"sprint wins\", \"from\": 3389, \"to\": 3400}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She comes into this event fresh off of five stage wins and the overall title victory at the Baloise Ladies Tour and she said she would spend time fine-tuning her form at home before heading to Paris.\", \"from\": 3402, \"to\": 3601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3595, \"end\": 3600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.65442159731475e-31, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this event\", \"from\": 3417, \"to\": 3427}, {\"ngram\": \"five stage wins\", \"from\": 3441, \"to\": 3456}, {\"ngram\": \"the overall title victory\", \"from\": 3461, \"to\": 3486}, {\"ngram\": \"the Baloise Ladies Tour\", \"from\": 3490, \"to\": 3513}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 3543, \"to\": 3547}, {\"ngram\": \"her form\", \"from\": 3560, \"to\": 3568}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 3572, \"to\": 3576}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wiebes will spearhead a Dutch team which also includes Tour de France winnerDemi Vollering, who could also win a medal in Paris, former multi-time world champion and Olympic championMarianne Vos,and three-time time trial world championEllen van Dijk.\", \"from\": 3603, \"to\": 3853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3627, \"end\": 3632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.565633213003175e-16, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 3658, \"end\": 3672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.753387942693707e-20, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 3725, \"end\": 3730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.65442159731475e